.SH "Name"
repo-add \- package database maintenance utility
.SH "Synopsis"
.sp
repo\-add [\-q] <path\-to\-db> <package1> [<package2> \&...]
.sp
repo\-remove [\-q] <path\-to\-db> <packagename> [<packagename2> \&...]
.SH "Description"
.sp
repo\-add and repo\-remove are two scripts to help build a package database for packages built with linkman:makepkg[8] and installed with linkman:pacman[8]\&.
.sp
repo\-add will update a package database by reading a built package file\&. Multiple packages to add can be specified on the command line\&.
.sp
repo\-remove will update a package database by removing the package name specified on the command line\&. Multiple packages to remove can be specified on the command line\&.
.SH "Options"
.PP
\fB\-q, \-\-quiet\fR
.RS 4
Force this program to keep quiet and run silent except for warning and error messages\&.
.RE
